               John Sculley, President
                  Kristina Hooper arranged a breakfast meeting, 1 Dec 87.  
                  General sort of "Get acquainted" talk.  Relevant highlights:
                  Paraphrasing him -- something like, "Apple is flying high, 
                  now, but I'm VERY nervous about how to turn Apple into the 
                  kind of company that it has to be to cope with its market in 
                  the next decade.  Traditional, large-company approach simply 
                  won't make it.
                  One action he has taken is to set up a task force to come up 
                  with a plan for the corporate information system that will be
                  flexible enough to support whatever form the company may need
                  to take.  Chartered three special people with this task:
                     His relatively new MIS VP; his Human Resorce Development 
                     director; and a legendary woman who created the 
                     super-modern Macintosh production factory.
                  As in every other first-exposure situation, Sculley didn't 
                  understand what Kristina and I told him about the "AUGMENT 
                  philosophy" for a strategic approach to the 
                  corporate-transformation problem.
                     Polite if not understanding:  he asked Kristina to set up 
                     a meeting with the MIS VIP.
               Alan Lauren, MIS VP
                  Kristina Hooper arranged a meeting on 16 Feb 88 in his office
                  at Apple headquarters.  He described their pursuit, and that 
                  it was rapidly gaining momentum in the company.
                  We got him to accept beng called "the Apple chaange agent" in
                  the spirit of the "AUGMENT philosophy."
                  Scully had accelerated the program to include it explictly in
                  the '89 budget plans.
                  Kristina made a pitch for Lauren to "buy into the bootstrap 
             strategy."  He wasn't against it; seemed to hear at least 
                  some of the concepts.
                  Lauren to leave for Europe; wanted to think about it.  Said 
                  that Harry Vertelney had given him a special presentation of 
                  his Spider project that morning -- an explortory use of 
                  exotic video linkage, coupled with hi-tech computer display, 
                  for collaboration between specially connected Apple people.  
                  So Lauren was primed to appreciate that technology was going 
                  to make significant differences. (Harry had given John Dutton
                  a quick description on 2 Feb).
               Current Status of Apple Liason
                  No further contact planned with either Sculley or Lauren.  
                  Decided instead to work on approach similar to taken with DEC
                  -- i.e. getting Apple people interested in participating with
                  the MDC pilots and the AUGMENT experience, then developing in
                  them the wider perceptions of potential organizational change
                  that would lead internally to involving their Apple-change 
                  activities.
                  Now, working through Harvey Lehtman to set up meeting with 
                  Dave Carter during week of 25 April.  Lehtman in best 
                  position within Apple to coordinate this, is making the 
                  contacts, and thinks it likely that we could arrange an Apple
                  group to visit MDC in STL for an exploratory discussion about
                  participation in the AUGMENT pilots in a manner similar to 
                  that under develoment with DEC.
            ON Technology
               Mitch Kapor was the founder and technical innovator behind Lotus
               123.  A year or so ago he pulled out of Lotus, apparently not 
               enjoying his role since the company had grown large.
               He has since started a company called "ON Technology," based in 
               Cambridge.  His goal is to bring out a line of products within 
               several years that, from his description, sounds very much akin 
