   SHORTFALLS / ASSISTANCE REQUIRED
      DECSYSTEM 2065 
         Progress is slower than planned in bringing the DEC 20 on line.  
         Missing equipment, malfunctioning equipment, and communication 
         problems have hampered the effort.  Thanks to Terry Schmidt the 
         equipment and system problems are being addressed. {TDC}
      MANAGEMENT DEFICIENCIES 
         Ability of the MDC St. Louis office to adequately plan, direct, and 
         control activities of the emerging pilots, coordinate the installation
         of the two DECsystem 2060's, coordinate interactions between DEC and 
         MDC, and effectively manage the day-to-day activities of the TAC group
         fall short of the desired results.  DEC has been made aware of our 
         perceived shortcomings and may provide assistance in the form of 
         on-site support personnel and specialized consultant support.  DEC is 
         interested in providing interactive support to insure that our pilot 
         projects are a success and to observe and document the pilot 
         evolutionary process. {DFY}
      NASP INTERACTIONS 
         Much more time needs to be spent with the NASP project members 
         discussing their requirements for use of Augment as a tool for 
         managing their project.  Key NASP project members have been 
         unavailable due to travel or other obligations. {TDC}
      NETWORK COMPUTING FORUM 
         Reassignment of Stephanie Victor to another project has crippled MDC 
         capability to participate effectively on the User Interface Working 
         Group.  We may have to withdraw from this activity. {TDC}
   NEXT MONTH's PLANS
      DEC/MDC JOINT ACTIVITIES
         An explicit business plan for tasks performed by joint teams will be 
         presented to MDC management.
         A task force will be assembled to update the specification and design 
         of the Augment front-end.  This effort is in preparation for porting 
         projects at DEC and MDC
      NASP PILOT PROJECT
         Personnel at the co-contractor and subcontractor locations will be 
         trained in the use of the Augment mail system.
         Expanded use of the Augment document capability will be pursued to 
         improve coordination on the NASP Materials Development Contract.
